# No Direct Prisma Usage

## Rule

`import { prisma } from "@lib/prisma"` is **never** allowed in any `.ts` file.

## Exceptions

The only file that may import `PrismaClient` directly is `src/lib/prisma.ts` (singleton export).

## How to Fix

Instead of direct Prisma calls, import functions from `@lib/db`:

```typescript
// BAD
import { prisma } from "@lib/prisma";
const dishes = await prisma.dish.findMany(...);

// GOOD
import { getDishes } from "@lib/db/dishes";
const dishes = await getDishes(...);
```

## Available Modules

- `@lib/db/dishes` - dishes CRUD
- `@lib/db/categories` - categories CRUD
- `@lib/db/menuStyles` - menu styles CRUD
- `@lib/db/tenants` - tenant queries
- `@lib/db/users` - user queries
- `@lib/db` - barrel export of all functions

## Adding New Functions

If you need a database function that doesn't exist, add it to the appropriate module in `src/lib/db/`. Never write direct Prisma calls in API routes, pages, or other application code.